Following a complete list of '''Australian animal extinctions''' from [[First Fleet|1788]] to the present. There are 23 birds, 4 frogs, and 27 mammal species or subspecies strongly believed to have become extinct since European settlement of Australia.
Extinctions are recorded under the ''[[Environment Protection and Biodiversity Conservation Act 1999]]''.
